Package com.epoch.exceptions

ACE-specific exceptions.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ConfigurationException
    Any problem with current configuration.
    DBException
    Thrown when any method cannot properly initialize the database objects.
    EquationFormatException
    Thrown when ACE cannot verify the response submitted by the user.
    FeedbackException
    Thrown when ACE needs to give feedback to a response submitted by the user.
    FileFormatException
    Thrown when any external file doesn't confirm to standards.
    GroupDefsException
    Thrown when there is a problem in the loading of functional or R group definitions.
    InvalidOpException
    Thrown when a method is called at an untimely instance.
    LicenseException
    Thrown when the number of searches performed exceeds the limit allowed by license.
    LimitException
    Thrown when any method violates the limit constraints.
    NonExistentException
    Thrown when ACE cannot find the specified item from the database.
    ParameterException
    Thrown when any method recieves an unexpected parameter.
    ParserException
    Thrown when there is an error parsing the external XML file.
    ProcessExecutionException
    Thrown when a runtime process called by ACE does not execute properly.
    ResponseFormatException
    Thrown when ACE cannot import or parse a response submitted by the user.
    ResponseParseException
    Thrown when ACE can import but cannot parse a response submitted by the user.
    StudentEmailExistsException
    Thrown when ACE attempts to register a student with an already existing email address.
    StudentNumConstraintException
    Thrown when ACE attempts to register a student with an already existing student number.
    UniquenessException
    Thrown when courseware cannot find the specified item from the database.
    ValenceException
    Thrown when a compound has a valence error.
    VerifyException
    Thrown when ACE cannot verify the response submitted by the user.
